3. FORMAL FMAPI MODEL

3.1 State Variables

We model the FM state as:

```
S = (T, D, P, E, O, L, R)
```

Variable Type Description
T Set of Tenants Identities with SPDM certificates
D Set of Devices Type-3 memory, DCD, etc.
P Set of Ports Physical ports (state: UP/DOWN)
E Set of Extents (base, length, tenant_id, zeroed_flag)
O: (D∪E) → T∪{⊥} Ownership Map Owner or unowned
L: T × D × E → {0,1} Allocation Map Which resources a tenant can access
R: T → ℕ Rate Counter Commands/sec per tenant

3.2 Valid Transitions

Example Valid Transitions:

Command Precondition Postcondition
Bind(t, d) O(d)=⊥ ∧ t∈T O(d)=t
Unbind(d) O(d)=t O(d)=⊥
SetPortState(p, DOWN) p∈P state(p)=DOWN
DCD_Add(e, t) O(e)=⊥ ∧ t∈T O(e)=t
DCD_Release(e) O(e)=t O(e)=⊥

3.3 Security Properties

Property Formal Definition
P1: Confinement ∀ r∈(D∪E), t1,t2∈T: (O(r)=t1 ∧ Access(t2,r)) ⇒ t1=t2
P2: Non-bypassability ∀ transition τ: Authorized(τ, caller) ∨ AdminOverride
P3: Availability ∀ t∈T: Rate(t) ≤ MAX_RATE(100/sec) ∧ FM responsive

